<section class="wrap">
  <div class="page-hero">
    <h1>How we verify every deal 🔍</h1>
    <p>Coupon sites are full of dead codes and fake "80% OFF" banners. We built IndiaOffers around one rule: nothing goes live until a human has checked it — and you can see when.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="prose">
    <h2>Our verification checklist</h2>
    <p>Before any deal is published on IndiaOffers.in, one of our deal hunters:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><b>Opens the actual product page</b> and confirms the deal price is live right now — not a cached price, not a screenshot from a Telegram forward.</li>
      <li><b>Checks the price against its recent history</b>, not the MRP. Indian e-commerce MRPs are routinely inflated 30–60%, so "70% OFF" often means nothing. We only call something a deal when it is genuinely at or near its recent low.</li>
      <li><b>Tests every coupon code</b> in a real cart before listing it. If a code is login-restricted, first-order-only or app-only, the deal page says so.</li>
      <li><b>Verifies stackable bank offers</b> against the banks' current offer terms, and computes your true effective price after stacking — the number we show as "best price".</li>
      <li><b>Compares across stores</b> — the same product is often listed on Amazon, Flipkart, Myntra and Ajio at different prices. We link the cheapest legitimate seller.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>The "last verified" timestamp</h2>
    <p>Every deal carries a visible <b>last verified</b> date — the last time a human re-checked it. Prices in India change fast; a deal verified today is near-certain to be live, one verified a week ago deserves a quick re-check at the store before you rely on it. We re-verify popular deals every time we touch them.</p>

    <h2>Expired deals retire automatically</h2>
    <p>Deals past their expiry date are removed from all listings automatically, every day. Their pages stay up marked <b>expired</b> — with live alternatives — so you are never tricked into chasing a dead price, and never land on a broken link from a search result.</p>

    <h2>What we will never do</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Post a deal we wouldn't use ourselves — no filler, no feed-dumped affiliate spam.</li>
      <li>Call an inflated-MRP discount a "deal".</li>
      <li>Let a commission decide our picks (see the affiliate disclosure below).</li>
      <li>Leave a known-dead coupon up to farm clicks.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Affiliate disclosure</h2>
    <p>Many outbound links on IndiaOffers.in are affiliate links — when you buy through them, the store may pay us a small commission at <b>no extra cost to you</b>. This funds the site, and it never affects which deals we publish: if a deal isn't genuinely great, it doesn't get posted, commission or not. Full details are in our <a href="/terms">Terms &amp; Conditions</a>.</p>

    <h2>Found a dead deal?</h2>
    <p>Tell us and we'll fix it fast — <a href="/contact">contact us</a> or WhatsApp us from any page. If you spot great deals before we do, <a href="/become-partner">become a partner</a> and earn rewards for submitting them.</p>
  </div>
</section>

